4) Create Dax Measures. 11

After we are done with the table relationship, now we can start creating calculated measures.

  • Click on the  red button above to download  the Zip file That contain all "the DAX formula needed" for the calculations.
  • Create the measures by order, because some measure's creation will require others to be created before.


STEP 1:

  • Select the table "TSA Claim" 

  • Click the new measure button on the ribbon.
  • Copy .# of Claims = COUNT('TSA Claim'[Claim ID]) From the Word File that you downloaded.
  • Past it in the measure Bar as Shown Below 



  • Repeat Step 1 for each Calculate that are in word File "the DAX formula needed".
  • after you are done, you should have a total of 7 measures as it shown bellow.
